<p>Our guides can help you with the basics of how to train your dog, but we also recommend <a href="/adviceandwelfare/pets/dogs/training/trainer">dog training classes</a> - especially for more advanced methods, such as clicker training.</p>

<p>If you have any problems, try asking a <a href="/adviceandwelfare/pets/general/findabehaviourist">qualified behaviourist</a> for advice. They specialise in behavioural issues such as excessive barking, aggression, destructiveness and phobias. You can also enlist the help of a dog training instructor if you need a bit of extra help.</p>
